msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:12
msgid ""
"After the system is installed, make sure that it's up to date with the "
"most recent security patches. Open a terminal window and issue the "
"following commands as root:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:14
msgid "``apt-get update``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:16
msgid "``apt-get upgrade``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:18
msgid "Install *sudo* and *curl* for use later in the installation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:20
msgid "``apt-get install sudo curl gnupg``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:22
msgid ""
"Add your username to the sudo group. In the following command, replace "
"{username} with your own username."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:24
msgid "``usermod -a -G sudo {username}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-server.rst:26
msgid ""
"Now that the system is up to date and our user is in the sudo group, you "
"can start installing the components that make up a Mattermost system."
msgstr ""

